<p>Abigail is a freelance director and associate director (new work and touring) of the Watermill Theatre. </p>

<p>As Director, theatre includes: <i>Bully</i> (Wales Millennium Centre); <i>Burke And Hare</i> (Jermyn Street Theatre – nominated, Off West End Award for Best Director and Best Ensemble; Watermill Theatre & UK tour); <i>Macbeth</i> (Big Brum, TIE tour); <i>Bee Happy</i> (The Old Red Lion Theatre); <i>The Tinderbox</i> (Charing Cross Theatre); <i>Baby</i> (The Hope Theatre); <i>Anna Weiss</i> (The Space – nominated, Off West End Award for Best Director); <i>Shrew</i> (international tour – nominated, Buxton Fringe Award for Best Production and Best New Writing and winner, Best Actress); <i>On Love</i> (The Bedford & Bike Shed Theatre).</p>

<p>Drama School productions include: <i>Life, Apparently</i> (Rose Bruford); <i>The Railway Children</i> (Mountview); <i>First Lady Suite</i> (Guildford School Of Acting); <i>Anna Karenina</i> (Read College); <i>The Believers</i> (Identity School Of Drama).</p>

<p>As Associate/Assistant Director: <i>The Nightingales</i> (Theatre Royal, Bath & UK tour); <i>Twelfth Night</i> (Wilton’s Music Hall); Violet, Harold And Maude, The Woman In White, Ragtime, Titanic, Death Takes A Holiday (Charing Cross Theatre); <i>Crazy For You</i> (Watermill Theatre & UK tour); <i>Twelfth Night, Romeo And Juliet</i> (Watermill Theatre & international tour); <i>Here Be Monsters, The Smallest Show On Earth</i> (UK tours); <i>Grand Hotel</i> (Southwark Playhouse); <i>The Wasp</i> (Hampstead Theatre); <i>The Grand Tour</i>  (Finborough Theatre); <i>The Adventures Of Pinnochio</i> (Watermill Theatre); <i>Pushing up Poppies</i> (Hill Street Theatre); <i>Much Ado About Nothing</i> (Guildford Shakespeare Company).</p>

